Official Go to website Live Demo Download A SASS mixin applies customizable NES-style pixelate borders to elements inspired by NES.css. ## How to use it:

Install & download.

```
# NPM
$ npm install pixel-borders --save
```

Import the pixel-borders. ```
@import "/path/to/pixel-borders.scss";
```

Customize the pixel borders using the following parameters: ```
@include pixel-borders(
  $corner-size: 1,                 
  $border-size: 4px, $border-color: #000,            
  $border-inset-color: false
);
@include pixel-box(
  $corner-size,
  $border-size, $background-color,              
  $border-color: false,           
  $border-inset: true, $border-inset-size: false,      
  $border-inset-color: false,     
  $border-inset-sides: false, $border-inset-color-br: false,
  $border-inset-color-tl: false
);
``` Add the CSS class`pixel-borders` to the target element. ```
