Here is the complete research report.

---

# Remilia Aesthetic + Gamified Web UI: Research Report

## 1. The Remilia Aesthetic -- What Makes It Distinct

### Visual DNA (from analyzing remilia.org, miladymaker.net, cult.inc)

**Color Palette:**
- Primary: Pure red (#FF0000) on black (#000000) -- this is the CULT.INC signature
- Secondary: White (#FFFFFF) on black for body text, thin red borders
- Remilia.org uses a different register: white/cream background with red accents and hand-drawn oval/elliptical borders
- Milady Maker uses soft pastel greens (#c7f090 mint backgrounds) with dark olive green text -- deliberately "web 1.0" feeling
- The overall ecosystem oscillates between two poles: **dark-terminal-red** (CULT) and **pastel-retro-soft** (Milady)

**Typography:**
- Monospace and bitmap fonts dominate -- visible on cult.inc which uses all-caps monospaced type
- Remilia.org uses a decorative serif/italic font for headings -- almost "corporate parody" calligraphic feel
- Milady Maker uses courier-style monospace, recalling GeoCities-era web
- Japanese characters mixed with English (e.g., "邪教公司 CULT, INC.") -- bilingual labeling is a signature move
- ALL-CAPS for navigation and section headers on the darker properties

**Layout Patterns:**
- remilia.org: Centered single-column with hand-drawn elliptical borders around navigation items -- the links are inside pill-shaped/oval containers with irregular borders
- cult.inc: Dark terminal aesthetic, single-column, hard 1px red borders forming rectangles, no rounded corners
- miladymaker.net: HTML table-era layout, no CSS framework, minimal styling, almost deliberately ugly
- Shared trait: deliberate rejection of modern design polish -- no gradients, no shadows, no glassmorphism

**Key Aesthetic Principles from Research:**
1. **Anti-polish / Deliberate crudeness** -- websites look intentionally unfinished, referencing early web
2. **Neochibi art** -- cute anime-derived characters with "affective flatness"
3. **Y2K nostalgia** -- pulling from late 90s/early 2000s Japanese web, FRUiTS magazine
4. **Post-ironic tone** -- simultaneously sincere and absurd
5. **Gamification as UX philosophy** -- RemiliaNET explicitly describes "Social Media as MMO" design philosophy, with achievement systems, social credit scores, leveling, unlockables
6. **Hypercitationalism** -- dense cultural references layered into every design decision

### RemiliaNET Design Philosophy (direct from their design notes)
From `blog.remilia.org/remilianet-alpha-design-notes/`:
- "Social Media as MMO" -- reimagine social network UX from the perspective of a massive-multiplayer game
- Achievement systems with point scoring (Beetlepoints)
- Generative sound effects on pentatonic scale for UX interactions
- "Layered Gaming" -- entire social ecosystem gamified with unlockables, rewards, randomization
- Generative avatars (Kagami) based on user ID
- User customizable hex-code theme colors that affect both personal UX and public profile

---

## 2. Gamified Web Interfaces -- Patterns and Examples

### RPG UI Elements for Web

**Health/Status Bars (HP, MP, XP):**
- Nested div approach: outer container (border + background) + inner fill div (colored, width controlled by percentage)
- Classic structure:
```html
<div class="status-bar">
  <div class="bar-label">HP</div>
  <div class="bar-track">
    <div class="bar-fill" style="width: 75%"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="bar-value">750/1000</div>
</div>
```

**Level/Rank Indicators:**
- Letter grading system (D, C, B, A, S, SS) -- Milady already uses this for their "Drip Score"
- XP progress toward next level as segmented bar
- Rank badges with metallic/textured borders

**Game UI Containers (Dialog boxes, panels):**
- RPGUI framework: lightweight library (25KB) for retro RPG-styled containers
- `border-image` with 9-slice scaling for custom frame borders
- Pixel-art border corners using box-shadow techniques

**Achievement Systems:**
- Grid of locked/unlocked badges with tooltips
- Progress percentage toward next achievement
- Rarity tiers with color coding (Common/Rare/Epic/Legendary)

**Key Reference Sites:**
- gameuidatabase.com -- 70,132+ screenshot database of actual game UIs
- RPGUI (github) -- CSS-only RPG-style UI components
- itch.io pixel UI packs -- reference for pixel-art styled interface elements

### Specific Game UI Paradigms Applicable to Recruitment

| Game Element | Recruitment Mapping |
|---|---|
| Character sheet | Candidate profile |
| Quest log | Job listings / application pipeline |
| Inventory | Skills/portfolio items |
| HP/MP bars | Profile completion / match score |
| Level/XP | Recruiter reputation / candidate rating |
| Achievement badges | Verified skills, completed interviews |
| Party system | Team hiring panels |
| Dungeon map | Hiring pipeline visualization |
| Boss battle | Final interview round |
| Loot drops | Candidate recommendations |
| Leaderboard | Top candidates / recruiters |

---

## 3. Actionable CSS Techniques

### A. CRT Scanline Effect

The definitive technique, sourced from multiple implementations:

```css
/* Overlay scanlines on any container */
.scanlines {
  position: relative;
}

.scanlines::before {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: 
    linear-gradient(
      rgba(18, 16, 16, 0) 50%, 
      rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.25) 50%
    ),
    linear-gradient(
      90deg, 
      rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.06), 
      rgba(0, 255, 0, 0.02), 
      rgba(0, 0, 255, 0.06)
    );
  background-size: 100% 2px, 3px 100%;
  z-index: 10;
  pointer-events: none;
}
```

The first gradient creates horizontal scanlines (alternating transparent and semi-transparent black every 2px). The second gradient creates subtle RGB sub-pixel simulation. Combined, they produce a convincing CRT monitor look.

### B. Screen Flicker

```css
.scanlines::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: rgba(18, 16, 16, 0.1);
  opacity: 0;
  z-index: 11;
  pointer-events: none;
  animation: flicker 0.15s infinite;
}

@keyframes flicker {
  0%   { opacity: 0.278; }
  10%  { opacity: 0.236; }
  20%  { opacity: 0.181; }
  30%  { opacity: 0.656; }
  40%  { opacity: 0.266; }
  50%  { opacity: 0.960; }
  60%  { opacity: 0.203; }
  70%  { opacity: 0.535; }
  80%  { opacity: 0.714; }
  90%  { opacity: 0.700; }
  100% { opacity: 0.244; }
}
```

### C. Moving Scanline Bar

```css
.moving-scanline {
  position: absolute;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100px;
  z-index: 12;
  background: linear-gradient(
    0deg,
    rgba(0, 0, 0, 0) 0%,
    rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2) 10%,
    rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1) 100%
  );
  opacity: 0.1;
  bottom: 100%;
  animation: scan-down 10s linear infinite;
  pointer-events: none;
}

@keyframes scan-down {
  0%   { bottom: 100%; }
  100% { bottom: -100px; }
}
```

### D. Neon Glow Effect

```css
/* Text glow */
.neon-text {
  color: #00f7ff;
  text-shadow: 
    0 0 5px #00f7ff,
    0 0 10px #00f7ff,
    0 0 20px #00f7ff,
    0 0 40px #00f7ff;
}

/* Box/border glow */
.neon-box {
  border: 2px solid #00f7ff;
  box-shadow: 
    0 0 10px #00f7ff,
    inset 0 0 5px #00f7ff;
}

/* Red variant (Remilia CULT style) */
.neon-red {
  color: #ff0000;
  text-shadow: 
    0 0 5px #ff0000,
    0 0 10px #ff0000,
    0 0 20px #ff3333;
  border-color: #ff0000;
  box-shadow: 
    0 0 10px rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5),
    inset 0 0 5px rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.3);
}
```

### E. Glitch Text Effect

```css
.glitch {
  position: relative;
  animation: text-glitch 6s ease-in-out infinite;
}

.glitch::before,
.glitch::after {
  content: attr(data-text);
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
}

.glitch::before {
  color: #ff00ea;
  z-index: -1;
  animation: glitch-shift 0.3s infinite alternate;
  clip-path: polygon(0 0, 100% 0, 100% 33%, 0 33%);
}

.glitch::after {
  color: #00f7ff;
  z-index: -2;
  animation: glitch-shift 0.3s infinite alternate-reverse;
  clip-path: polygon(0 66%, 100% 66%, 100% 100%, 0 100%);
}

@keyframes glitch-shift {
  0%   { transform: translate(0); }
  25%  { transform: translate(-3px, 1px); }
  50%  { transform: translate(2px, -1px); }
  75%  { transform: translate(-1px, 2px); }
  100% { transform: translate(3px, -2px); }
}
```

### F. Pixel Borders (using border-image)

```css
/* Option 1: CSS-only pixel border using box-shadow */
.pixel-border {
  --pixel: 4px;
  box-shadow:
    /* top */
    calc(var(--pixel) * 1)  0 0 0 currentColor,
    calc(var(--pixel) * -1) 0 0 0 currentColor,
    /* corners get stepped for pixel look */
    0 calc(var(--pixel) * 1) 0 0 currentColor,
    0 calc(var(--pixel) * -1) 0 0 currentColor;
}

/* Option 2: border-image with SVG for RPG-style frames */
.rpg-frame {
  border: 12px solid transparent;
  border-image-source: url('data:image/svg+xml,...'); /* 9-slice SVG */
  border-image-slice: 12 fill;
  border-image-repeat: stretch;
}

/* Option 3: SASS mixin approach (pixel-borders npm package) */
/* npm install pixel-borders --save */
/* @include pixel-borders($corner-size: 1, $border-size: 4px, $border-color: #ff0000); */
```

### G. HP/XP Progress Bars

```css
.game-bar {
  --fill: 75%;
  --bar-color: #ff3333;
  --bar-bg: #1a0000;

  position: relative;
  width: 100%;
  height: 24px;
  background: var(--bar-bg);
  border: 2px solid var(--bar-color);
  overflow: hidden;
}

.game-bar::before {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  inset: 2px;
  width: calc(var(--fill) - 4px);
  background: linear-gradient(
    180deg,
    color-mix(in srgb, var(--bar-color), white 30%) 0%,
    var(--bar-color) 50%,
    color-mix(in srgb, var(--bar-color), black 30%) 100%
  );
  transition: width 0.5s ease;
}

/* Animated shimmer overlay */
.game-bar::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: repeating-linear-gradient(
    -45deg,
    transparent,
    transparent 8px,
    rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05) 8px,
    rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05) 16px
  );
  animation: bar-shimmer 1s linear infinite;
}

@keyframes bar-shimmer {
  from { transform: translateX(-16px); }
  to   { transform: translateX(16px); }
}

/* Color variants */
.game-bar.hp   { --bar-color: #ff3333; --bar-bg: #1a0000; }
.game-bar.mp   { --bar-color: #3366ff; --bar-bg: #000a1a; }
.game-bar.xp   { --bar-color: #ffcc00; --bar-bg: #1a1500; }
.game-bar.stam { --bar-color: #33ff33; --bar-bg: #001a00; }
```

